===Noun===
'''flatus''' (''plural:'' '''[[flatuses]]''')

#Wind or gas generated in the stomach or other cavities of the body.

===Usage note===
As '''flatus''' is a noun from Latin’s [[Appendix:Latin fourth declension|fourth declension]], its etymologically–derived plural is formed by lengthening the ‘u’ (written identically, or with a macron as flatūs) — as in the words [[impetus]] and [[prospectus]]. Unlike other Latin rules for forming plurals (such as “a→ae”, “us→i”, “um→a”), the “us→ūs” rule is seldom if ever used in English; the “-es” suffix is used instead.

